Scroll to the bottom of any page to locate the footer. 2. Under **"Our Company"**, click on any of the links: - About us - Vacancies - Contact us - Privacy - Returns policy 3. Observe that no redirection or page load happens. #### Issue 2: No Scroll-to-Top Button 1. Scroll down a long page. 2. Look for a floating "Scroll to Top" button (usually bottom-right corner). 3. Observe that no such button is present. --- ### **Expected Behavior** - **Footer Links:** Each link should navigate to its respective page or section: - **About us** â†’ `/about` - **Vacancies** â†’ `/vacancies` - **Contact us** â†’ `/contact` - **Privacy** â†’ `/privacy` - **Returns policy** â†’ `/returns` - and many other links in footer should navigate. - **Scroll-to-Top Button:** A visible button should appear after scrolling down, allowing the user to instantly return to the top of the page. --- ### **Actual Behavior** - Footer links do not navigate anywhere. - No "Scroll to Top" button is available on the website. --- ### **ðŸ”—Attachments** - No Scroll-to-top button in corner and footer links not redirecting. --- ### **QA Checklist After Fix** - [ ] All footer links navigate to correct pages. - [ ] Scroll-to-top button appears after scrolling down. - [ ] Scroll-to-top button smoothly scrolls the page to the top.

### âœ¨ Feat: Add Audio Classification

### Description

This PR implements a complete, memory-efficient audio classification pipeline for real-time inference on ESP32. It successfully processes audio from an I2S microphone, extracts features, and runs a TFLite model to classify audios.



### ðŸš€ **How It Works**

The data flows through a simple, 4-stage pipeline:

1.  ðŸŽ¤ **Audio Capture**: Reads `44032` 16-bit PCM samples from an I2S microphone.
2.  ðŸ”¬ **Feature Extraction**: Converts audio to a `9976`-element feature vector (`43 frames Ã— 232 features`) .
3.  ðŸ§  **Model Inference**: The TFLite engine performs `int8` quantized inference on an embedded model. It internally handles all `float32` â†” `int8` conversions.
4.  ðŸ“Š **Results**: Outputs `float32` probabilities for 3 classes: "Background Noise", "one", and "two".



### ðŸ› ï¸ **Key Architectural Features**

*   **Modular Design**: Built with standardized `Sensor`, `Processor`, and `Engine` components for easy extension and testing.
*   **Memory-Efficient**: Leverages PSRAM for large buffers (`heap_caps`), employs RAII for automatic cleanup, and minimizes data copies.
*   **Optimized Performance**: Uses **KissFFT** for fast spectral analysis and **Int8 Quantization** for accelerated TFLite inference.
*   **Robust & Safe**: Implements clear `core::Status` error handling and C++ template-based type safety.



### ðŸ“‚ **Core Components Changed**

*   **`InferencePipeline`**: Orchestrates the entire data flow.
*   **`FeatureExtractor`**: Implements the STFT-based feature generation logic.
*   **`TFLiteEngine`**: Wraps the TFLite Micro interpreter, handling model loading and inference.
*   **`MicrophoneI2S`**: Provides the hardware audio capture interface.
*   **`main.cpp` (Example)**: Demonstrates the end-to-end usage of the pipeline.



### âœ… **Verification**

The full pipeline has been tested on hardware and successfully classifies audio in real-time. The architecture is now stable and ready for further feature development.

issue.title: Missing SNES DAT generation when using -dat option
issue.body:
## Bug Description
  When using the `-dat` command line option, the SNES DAT file is not generated despite SNES support being available in FBNeo.

  ## Expected Behavior
  Running `./fbneo -dat` should generate a `FBNeo_-_Super_Nintendo_Entertainment_System.dat` file containing all supported SNES ROMs.

  ## Actual Behavior
  The SNES DAT file is not created. Only other system DAT files are generated (Arcade, NES, FDS, Neo Geo Pocket, etc.).

  ## Environment
  - **Platform**: Linux
  - **Version**: Latest master branch (commit 2fd36bd68)
  - **Build**: SDL2
  - **Command used**: `./fbneo -dat`

  ## Technical Details
  The `DAT_SNES_ONLY` constant is defined in `src/burner/burner.h:270` and properly handled in `src/burner/dat.cpp`, but the actual generation calls are missing from the
   `generateDats()` function in `src/burner/sdl/main.cpp`.

  Looking at the code, all other DAT types defined in `burner.h` are properly generated in the `generateDats()` function except SNES:
  - âœ… DAT_ARCADE_ONLY â†’ generates FBNeo_-_Arcade.dat
  - âœ… DAT_NES_ONLY â†’ generates FBNeo_-_Nintendo_Entertainment_System.dat
  - âœ… DAT_FDS_ONLY â†’ generates FBNeo_-_Nintendo_Famicom_Disk_System.dat
  - âŒ DAT_SNES_ONLY â†’ **missing generation call**
  - âœ… DAT_NGP_ONLY â†’ generates FBNeo_-_Neo_Geo_Pocket.dat

  ## Suggested Fix
  Add the missing calls in `src/burner/sdl/main.cpp` around lines 173-174:

  ```cpp
  _stprintf(filename, _T("%sFBNeo_-_Super_Nintendo_Entertainment_System.dat"), szAppDatListsPath);
  create_datfile(filename, DAT_SNES_ONLY);

  And around lines 231-232 for SDL1.2 compatibility:
  sprintf(filename, "FBNeo_-_Super_Nintendo_Entertainment_System.dat");
  create_datfile(filename, DAT_SNES_ONLY);
